Download Java 8 jdk (Skip this step if installed)
https://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jdk8-downloads-2133151.html

To set java on Linux 

1) move tar.gz file to required location and run this command

$ sudo tar xvzf YOUR_JDK_DOWNLOADED_FILE.tar.gz 

2) now to set your JAVA_HOME environment variable by these :

$ JAVA_HOME=/usr/java/jdk_YOUR_VERSION_NAME/
$ sudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/java java ${JAVA_HOME%*/}/bin/java 20000
$ sudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/javac javac ${JAVA_HOME%*/}/bin/javac 20000


To set default java

$ update-alternatives --config java
 
a output showing different jdks available on system appears like this

There are 2 choices for the alternative java (providing /usr/bin/java).

  Selection    Path                                           Priority   Status
------------------------------------------------------------
* 0            /opt/java/jdk1.8.0_05/bin/java                  20000     auto mode
  1            /opt/java/jdk1.8.0_05/bin/java                  20000     manual mode
  2            /usr/lib/jvm/java-6-openjdk-i386/jre/bin/java   1061      manual mode

Press enter to keep the current choice[*], or type selection number:



